sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K395105
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: GFP reporter repressed by LuxR and 3OC6HSL (K395008:K121013)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is GFP reporter which is represed by LuxR and 3OC6HSL, and the promoter is K395008. And we use this part to measure the activity of BBa_K395008.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Shohei Kitano

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K395008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Repressed by protein LuxR and 3OC6HSL. The consensus sequence of -35 and -10 is the same as that of BBa_J23108.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Eriko Uchikoshi
